### Retrieve a list of all students
GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/students
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Retrieve details of a student by ID (replace {id} with an actual ID)
GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/students/1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Add a new student (Student 1)
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Michael Johnson",
    "grade": "A",
    "email": "michael.johnson@example.com"
}

###

### Add a new student (Student 2)
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Emily Davis",
    "grade": "B",
    "email": "emily.davis@example.com"
}

###

### Update the first student by ID (Student 1, ID 1)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:5000/students/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Johnathan Doe",
    "grade": "A+",
    "email": "johnathandoe@example.com"
}

###

### Delete the second student by ID (Student 2, ID 2)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:5000/students/2
Content-Type: application/json
